squish
------------------------------------------
The squish library (abbreviated to libsquish) is an open source DXT
compression library written in C++ with the following features:
 * Supports the DXT1, DXT3 and DXT5 formats.
 * Optimised for both SSE and Altivec SIMD instruction sets.
 * Builds on multiple platforms (x86 and PPC tested).
 * Very simple interface.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.35-1
  libgcc1-4.9.2-3
  libpng16-1.6.16-1
  libsquish-devel-1.11+svn60-1bl1
  libsquish0.0-1.11+svn60-1bl1
  libstdc++6-4.9.2-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.25-1
  cmake-3.1.2-1
  cygport-0.18.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-3
  gcc-g++-4.9.2-3
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://www.sjbrown.co.uk/squish/

Canonical download:
  http://libsquish.googlecode.com/svn

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack squish-1.11+svn60-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./squish-1.11+svn60-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/squish-1.11+svn60-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/squish-1.11+svn60-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsquish0.0-1.11+svn60-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsquish-devel-1.11+svn60-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(squish)
  /usr/bin/squishpng.exe
  /usr/bin/squishtest.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/squish.README
  /usr/share/doc/squish/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/squish/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/squish/README

(libsquish0.0)
  /usr/bin/cygsquish-0.0.dll

(libsquish-devel)
  /usr/include/squish.h
  /usr/lib/libsquish.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/squish.pc

